The paper deals with generative shape modeling in computer vision and interactive computer graphics, which is a common research area in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The proposed model uses a conditional GAN, which is a popular deep learning technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses a user study, which falls under the category of social and information sciences (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
